1. Sicelides Musae. The Sicilian Muses are spoken of as the friends of pastoral poetry. This kind of poetry flourished in Sicily: Theocritus, Moschus, and Bion, the most distinguished writers of Greek pastor-als, either were born or resided in that island.—Virgil calls upon the Pas- toral Muses to aid him while he attempts a higher strain.
